In this speech at Viasat Corporate Headquarters in Carlsbad, California, President Biden thanks the audience for their service and discusses the importance of supporting veterans and their families. He mentions his wife's initiative, Joining Forces, which focuses on supporting military families during deployments. He emphasizes the sacred obligation to care for and support veterans and highlights the bipartisan efforts to pass bills that improve veterans' lives. President Biden also discusses the CHIPS and Science Act, a law that aims to boost semiconductor manufacturing in the United States, which is crucial for national security and the economy. He mentions the investments being made in research and development, clean energy, and infrastructure. President Biden also addresses the issue of inflation and discusses measures being taken to reduce prescription drug costs and address climate change. He concludes by expressing optimism about the future of the United States.